# UI & Localization

## No hardcoded user-facing strings

Every string shown to the user comes from `AppLocalizations`.

```dart
final l10n = AppLocalizations.of(context)!;
Text(l10n.familyNetWorth); // GOOD
Text('家庭净资产');          // BAD
```

To add copy: edit `lib/l10n/app_en.arb` + `app_zh.arb`, then run
`flutter gen-l10n` (or build). Seed/dev-only text that is intentionally not
localized belongs in `lib/core/app_constants.dart`.

## Formatting

Use helpers in `lib/core/utils/formatters.dart` (`formatMoney`,
`formatSignedMoney`, `formatDate`, ...) with the current locale; never format
money/dates by hand.

## Widgets

- Read data via `ref.watch(provider)` and handle `loading` / `error` with
  `AsyncValue.when`.
- Prefer `StatelessWidget` when a widget only renders passed-in data (e.g. pass
  a precomputed forecast in rather than re-reading a provider).
- Use `(_, _)` for unused callback params (not `(_, __)`).
